National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Akif Cağatay Kiliç, Spokesperson and Chief Advisor to the President of Türkiye. Sullivan congratulated Kiliç on his new position and expressed readiness to work together to strengthen the bilateral partnership and address shared challenges. They discussed recent developments in Russia and the United States' support for Ukraine in defending against Russian aggression. They also talked about Türkiye's efforts to renew the Black Sea Grain Initiative and the importance of stability in the Aegean, with Sullivan welcoming engagement between Türkiye and Greece. They also discussed preparations for the upcoming NATO Summit in Vilnius, with Sullivan emphasizing the United States' view that Sweden should become a NATO member as soon as possible.